vulnerability.name: USN-7080-1
vulnerability.description: Toshifumi Sakaguchi discovered that Unbound incorrectly handled name  compression for large RRsets, which could lead to excessive CPU usage.  An attacker could potentially use this issue to cause a denial of service by sending specially crafted DNS responses.

statements.status_notes: Unbound could be made to stop responding if it received specially crafted DNS traffic.
